FTSE-100 Stocks Climb in London as Barclays, RBS, Lloyds Shares Lead Gain

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-08-12T07:48:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/ftse-100-stocks-climb-in-london-as-barclays-rbs-lloyds-shares-lead-gain.html
U.K. stocks climbed, erasing earlier
losses as banks advanced in  London  trading.  The FTSE 100 Index rose 0.6 percent to 5,101.04 at 8:47
a.m. in London after earlier falling as much as 1.2 percent.  Barclays Plc rallied 3.9 percent to 184.75 pence and Royal
Bank of Scotland Group Plc gained 2.7 percent to 25.94 pence.  Arm Holdings Plc still paced declining shares, falling 1.3
percent to 513.5 pence.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  